OpenFlow.NBAPI
Class SBMatchFilterSpec

java.lang.Object
  OpenFlow.NBAPI.SBMatchFilterSpec
Direct Known Subclasses:
FlowModSpec, NBMatchFilterSpec
public class SBMatchFilterSpec
extends java.lang.Object

Aids in creation of OFMatchPB objects.

Provides get/set convenience methods that ensure consistency with the SB wildcards match field. In general, setting a null value toggles on the corresponding wild-card flag whereas setting an actual value toggles it off. Minimal range checking is performed on values (i.e., that they are within range of the target SB message field element size) for all set<Field>() methods that return a boolean. Otherwise, no range checking is performed on the field values.

Performs comparison of match criteria restricted to protocol/address/port information.

Parameters:
other - The other spec to compare against
unrestricted - if true, the following fields are included in the comparison: OFWildcardFlagsPB.OFPFW_IN_PORT, OFWildcardFlagsPB.OFPFW_DL_VLAN, OFWildcardFlagsPB.OFPFW_DL_VLAN_PCP, and OFWildcardFlagsPB.OFPFW_NW_TOS. Otherwise, these fields are excluded from the comparison of match criteria.

setFrom

public void setFrom(org.openflow.northboundapi.proto.SBOFMatchesPB.OFMatchPB pkt_data,
                    boolean unrestricted)
Set match criteria from an immutable OFMatchPB object.

This method is a convenience method to set match criteria from an immutable OFMatchPB object that was received as a component of a packet-in message. As such, the wildcards field of the OFMatchPB in this case is generally uninformative and/or unreliable and is ignored by this method (only a field's PB presence is checked, not its "wildcard" state).

Parameters:
pkt_data - The immutable OFMatchPB object criteria source
unrestricted - if true, the following fields are included (if present) in the match criteria: OFPFW_IN_PORT, OFPFW_DL_VLAN, OFPFW_DL_VLAN_PCP, OFPFW_NW_TOS, OFPFW_TP_SRC, and OFPFW_TP_DST. Otherwise, these fields are excluded from setting the match criteria, except for "TP_SRC" and "TP_DST" which are set only if "OFPFW_DL_TYPE" is IPv4 and "OFPFW_NW_PROTO" is either TCP or UDP.
